(1823, 17, 'Real-World Simulation Create a class hierarchy Payment → CreditCardPayment, GcashPayment, and BankTransfer. Each overrides processPayment() with unique details. Demonstrate how a single method call handles multiple payment types dynamically.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Intermediate', 'Simulation question'),
(1824, 17, 'Polymorphic Collections with ArrayList Create a superclass Shape with subclasses Circle, Square, and Rectangle. Store them in an ArrayList<Shape>, iterate through the list, and call getArea() for each object.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Intermediate', 'Simulation question'),
(1825, 17, 'Using Abstract Classes for Transport Create an abstract class Transport with an abstract method start(). Subclasses Bus, Train, and Airplane each override start() differently. Demonstrate polymorphism with a method beginTransport(Transport t) that calls t.start().', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Intermediate', 'Simulation question'),
(1826, 17, 'Interface for Payment System Create an interface Payable with method pay(). Implement it in classes CashPayment, CardPayment, and OnlinePayment. Demonstrate how different payment modes behave polymorphically through a single Payable reference.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Intermediate', 'Simulation question'),
(1827, 30, 'Applying Inline CSS Create a simple HTML page with a heading and a paragraph. Use inline CSS to set: Heading color to blue Paragraph text color to gray', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
(1828, 30, 'Internal vs. External CSS Create a webpage with: One heading styled using internal CSS One paragraph styled using external CSS (linked .css file) Show that both styles apply correctly.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
(1829, 30, 'Changing Background Colors Design a page with three sections: header, main, and footer. Use CSS to: Give each section a different background color. Set the text color to white.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
(1830, 30, 'Font Styling Create a webpage that uses: Font family: Arial Font size: 18px Font style: italic Apply these to all paragraphs using CSS selectors.', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
(1831, 30, 'CSS Selectors Practice Create an HTML page with: 2 headings (<h1>, <h2>) 2 paragraphs 1 span with the class \"highlight\" Use: Element selector for <h1> ID selector for #mainText', 'Class selector for .highlight', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
(1832, 30, 'Borders and Padding Create a <div> with some text inside. Use CSS to: Add a solid border of 2px (color of your choice) Add padding of 15px Give the <div> a background color', '', '', '', '', 'A', 'Beginner', 'Simulation question'),
